				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\%$$\end{document} in the case of Solarex MSX83 solar cell. Hence, ideality factor ‘n’ is categorized as ”Sensitive parameter”. Apart from individual contribution, variance in the output can also be quantified using mutual interaction between two or more parameters. Based on second-order Sobol indices, ideality factor ‘n’, photocurrent ‘IPh\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
